---
source: plasm-oss/crates/plasm-core/src/prompt_render.rs
expression: render_plasm_mcp_language_frontmatter()
---
This defines valid Plasm syntax for this prompt; reply with one valid plasm_program:

Output:
- Single `plasm_expr` iff one lookup/query/search/relation/method/action is the whole answer.
- Else one multi-line `plasm_program`: bind → narrow (projection/postfix/bracket-render) → small bare roots—not many one-line tool calls.

Grammar (pseudo-EBNF; DOMAIN rows instantiate `plasm_expr` atoms):
plasm_program ::= plasm_roots | binding+ plasm_roots
binding       ::= ident "=" plasm_node
plasm_roots   ::= plasm_return ("," plasm_return)*
plasm_return  ::= node_ref | plasm_expr
plasm_node    ::= ( plasm_expr | node_ref ) postfix* bracket_render_tail? | node_ref "=>" plasm_value | node_ref "=>" effect_expr
plasm_expr    ::= entity_expr [projection]
entity_expr   ::= query_all | get | query | relation | method | create_action | search
query_all     ::= e#
get           ::= e#(id) or e#(p#=v, p#=v)
query         ::= e#{p#=v, …}
relation      ::= e#(id).p#
method        ::= e#(id).m#() or e#(id).m#(p#=v,..)
create_action ::= e#.m#(args)
search        ::= e#~"text"
projection    ::= e#(id)[p#,…] | "[" fields "]"
postfix       ::= transform | "[" fields "]"
bracket_render_tail ::= ( "[" fields "]" )? "<<TAG" heredoc_body "TAG"
positive_int  ::= non-zero decimal integer literal
agg_func      ::= "sum" | "avg" | "min" | "max"
agg_spec      ::= ident "=" ( "count" | agg_func "(" field ")" )
agg_specs     ::= agg_spec ("," agg_spec)*
sort_dir      ::= omitted | "desc" | "asc" | "ascending" | "descending"
transform     ::= ".limit(" positive_int ")" | ".sort(" field ["," sort_dir] ")" | ".aggregate(" agg_specs ")" | ".group_by(" field "," agg_specs ")" | ".singleton()" | ".page_size(" positive_int ")"
fields        ::= [p#,…]
plasm_value   ::= literal | node_ref | node_ref.field | _.field | [v, …]
effect_expr   ::= taught write/update/delete/action surface from DOMAIN (same line may template rows)
ident/node_ref/field ::= agent-chosen names for bound nodes and fields
literal       ::= quoted string | number | bool | null | heredoc

Aggregates (examples): `.aggregate(n=count)`, `.aggregate(total=sum(amount), lo=min(price))`, `.group_by(author, n=count)`.

Continuation:
- Postfix (transforms, `[fields]`, `<<TAG…TAG`) may chain on one surface `plasm_expr`.
- `ident.<relation>` only after surface row bindings (get/query/relation); after projection/transform/`=>`, repeat full DOMAIN expr or rebind. Bracket-render = Minijinja `rows`; optional `[fields]` narrows columns → row `{"content":"…"}` — use **`binding.content`** for string/body args.

MCP `program` (JSON string):
- Literal U+000A between statements (one `ident = …` per line; bare roots last). Spaces never separate statements.
- Heredoc: newline after `<<TAG` opener; close line trims to `TAG` / `TAG)` / `TAG,` / `TAG}`; first matching trimmed interior line closes—opaque `TAG` for blobs. Commas inside heredocs never split roots (e.g. `…<<B` / `Hello` / `B` / `), e2`).

Discipline:
- Plan shape first; small roots unless raw rows requested; bracket-render row-derived text, static `<<TAG` for fixed payloads.
- `page(sN_pgM)` continues a chosen list only; DOMAIN is the shape contract—no probe calls.

DOMAIN / catalogue:
- `plasm_expr` = atoms; `Meaning` = how to pick/fill—never paste `Meaning`. Bare comma-separated roots (no `return`); every symbol taught here.
- Projection: minimal non-empty `[p#,…]`; identity row lists full fields once. Leading `p#` rows = slot metadata when method `args:` is insufficient.
- e#, m#, p# are session-local aliases — copy them exactly; new prompts supersede old meanings.
- Pick by `Meaning`, copy `plasm_expr`, bind keyed slot (`p12=value`) only; never positional or renumbered args.
- Instantiate grammar lines from DOMAIN only; keyed `p#=v` never positional. `v=$` in tables is a fill cue.
- `e#{p#=v, …}` / `e#` list/filter; `e#(id) or e#(p#=v, p#=v)` fetch one; `e#(id).p#` relate; `e#(id).m#() or e#(id).m#(p#=v,..)` call; `e#.m#(args)` without id; `e#(id)[p#,…]` projects—after `e#(id)`, `.` is relation or taught `m#` only.
- Scoped child lists: `X{p#=AnchorEntity(id)}` from the child entity’s DOMAIN rows; never invent `Y(id).p#`.
- Arrays in args: `[v, …]` (e.g. `p#=[e#($)]`). Quoted strings: only `\"` and `\\` escapes.
- `select` one allowed value; `multiselect` / multi-value lists as `[v, …]`.
- `markdown`/`html`/`document`/`json_text`/`blob` values (per `Meaning`): `<<TAG` … `TAG` only; e.g. `m#(..., p#=<<TXT` + newline body + `TXT` newline `)`.
- Search `e#~"text"` only where DOMAIN teaches `~` on that entity.
- `p#`-only rows declare slots (metadata), not expressions to emit.
- `$` marks fill-ins — substitute real values; never send `$`.
- `..` — optional trailing params (`optional params:` lists them); `..` alone means all args optional.
